      "ESSeqNum": 2,
      "FacilityID": 1000063013,
      "SummaryText": "sudden chemical releases, natural events, public hazards (i.e., bomb threats, riots, etc.) or oil spills related to daily operations at the Plant.  The Contingency Plan mirrors the Emergency Response and Disaster Control Plan in terms of response method and response team organization to ensure consistency between the two Plans.   \r\n\r\nPursuant to the requirements of the December 5, 2008 amendments to Title 40 of the Code of Federal Regulations Part 112 (40 CFR 112), as well as the Code of Maryland Regulations (COMAR) 26.10.01 governing oil pollution and tank management rules, the Plant has developed and implemented a SPCC Plan.   The SPCC Plan was prepared to address federal and state requirements for response to and prevention of spills.  Applicable regulations regarding spill prevention, reporting, and response are:\r\n\u00bf\t40 CFR 112 - Environmental Protection Agency Regulations on Oil Pollution Prevention;\r\n\u00bf\t40 CFR 110 - Discharge of Oil;\r\n\u00bf\t40 CFR 117 and 40 CFR 302.4 - Determination of Reportable Quantities for Hazardous Substances;\r\n\u00bf\t40 CFR 302 - Designation, Reportable Quantities and Notification;\r\n\u00bf\t40 CFR 300 - National Oil and Hazardous Substances Pollution Contingency Plan; \r\n\u00bf\t40 CFR 355 - Emergency Planning and Notification; and \r\n\u00bf\tCOMAR 26.10.01.12 - Requirements for Above-Ground Oil Storage Facilities\r\n\r\nThe SPCC Plan is maintained by the Environmental Engineer.  Updates to the SPCC Plan will occur whenever there are changes to the processes taking place at the Plant which could affect storage of petroleum products.  \r\n\r\n\u00bf\tGeneral Accidental Release Prevention Program And Chemical-Specific Prevention Steps Emergency Response Program\r\n\r\nAn emergency response program was developed for the purpose of protecting the Plant employee's health and to protect the environment.   The Plant emergency response program includes the following elements: \r\n\r\n\u00bf\tThe Plant has developed and implemented an Emergency Response Procedure (Procedure) which meets the emergency r"
